# Docker — Testcontainers

Client and server integration tests start an ActiveMQ Artemis container via Testcontainers. **Docker must be available** when running `mvn verify` or module integration tests.

## Commands

```bash
mvn verify
mvn -pl client test
mvn -pl server test
```

## Local broker (optional)

Without Testcontainers, for manual exploration:

```bash
docker compose -f scripts/docker/docker-compose.yaml up
```

Ports: STOMP TCP 61613, WebSocket 61614, OpenWire 61616, console 8161.

## Do not

- Assume integration tests pass without Docker.
- Commit changes that break `StompContainer` startup without updating test resources (`broker.xml`).

## When changing test infra

- Update `client/src/test/resources/broker.xml` and `StompContainer` if broker config changes.
- Document new ports or env in [ARCHITECTURE.md](../../ARCHITECTURE.md) §9 and [development-experience.mdc](development-experience.mdc).
